Bring a large #saucepan{} of @water{550%ml} to the boil. Once boiling add the @chicken stock powder{1} and the @tomato passata{1} and stir thoroughly to dissolve the stock powder. Turn the heat to low.

> Keep the stock on the lowest heat to keep it hot during the whole cooking process.

Halve, peel and finely chop the @onion{1}(peeled and finely chopped). Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Roughly chop the @flat leaf parsley{1/2}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Remove the skin from the @Tuscan pork sausage{4} and break the sausage meat into chunks.

> Remember to wash your hands and equipment after handling raw meat.

Heat a splash of @olive oil{1%splash} in another large saucepan on medium-low heat. Add the onion and sausage chunks. Cook until the onion is soft and the sausage is no longer pink, ~{6-7%minutes}. Add the garlic. Cook for a further ~{1%minute}. Add the @Arborio rice{175%g} and @fennel seeds{1}. Stir together to make sure the rice is coated in oil.

> Add less fennel if you don't love the aniseedy flavour.

If you have some @?white wine{splash} in your kitchen, add a splash now.

> Let the alcohol in the wine bubble off for a few minutes to mellow the flavour. If you don't have any wine don't worry, just move right on to the next step. The risotto will still taste delicious!

Add a ladleful of the stock and passata mix to the rice and stir it in gently. Once the liquid is almost fully absorbed, add another ladleful and continue stirring. Keep adding the stock and passata mix, stirring all the time until the rice is cooked, ~{15-20%minutes}.

> If you've added all the stock but the rice isn't quite there, just add a splash of water and continue cooking. The sausage meat is cooked when it is no longer pink in the middle.

Once your risotto is ready, add a splash of water if it is too thick. The ideal risotto should flow like lava! Stir in the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and @unsalted butter{15%g}. Test for seasoning and add @salt{to taste} and @ground black pepper{to taste}. Serve in warm #bowls{} with a sprinkling of parsley and eat immediately. Enjoy!